{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PuGrmGhhcnJRW6PUKzWsbk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"As I suspected: `platform` depends on `rng-shared`, and `rng-shared` would need to depend on `platform` (with `cpi` feature) for the CPI helper. That's a circular dependency.\n\nThe solution is to NOT put the actual `platform::cpi::update_player_profile` call in the shared crate. Instead, I need to construct the CPI instruction manually, without importing the `platform` crate.\n\nHow does Anchor CPI work?\n1. The `platform::cpi::update_player_profile` function creates a CPI instruction that calls the platform program's `update_player_profile` instruction\n\n\n2. It sets up the accounts using the `UpdatePlayerProfile` accounts struct and serializes the instruction data with the function discriminator and arguments\n\nI can replicate this manually by computing the instruction discriminator from the SHA256 hash of `\"global:update_player_profile\"`, serializing the arguments, creating an `Instruction` directly, and invoking it with `anchor_lang::solana_program::program::invoke_signed`. This sidesteps the circular dependency while achieving the same result. I'll implement this by checking if the profile is empty first, then building the instruction manually.\n\nNow I'm looking at the function signature from the spec and realizing there's a mismatch between what the platform's instruction expects—`(wager_amount, won_amount, is_winner)`—and what the spec defines with the delta parameters.\n\nSince the platform increments `total_games` by 1 automatically, `total_games_delta` is essentially fixed at 1 per call, and `wins_delta` maps to whether `is_winner` is true. The wagered and won amounts map directly to their respective deltas. I'll implement the spec's signature as-is and handle the parameter mapping internally.\n\nRather than risk a circular dependency with the platform program's types, I should construct the CPI instruction manually by computing the discriminator myself.\n\nComputing the discriminator...\n\nI need to create a function that computes the SHA256 hash of \"global:update_player_profile\" and extracts the first 8 bytes as the discriminator. Then I'll manually serialize the instruction data using Borsh encoding, starting with those 8 discriminator bytes followed by the wager and won amounts as little-endian u64 values. Writing the CPI helper function... Building the instruction and account metadata...\n\nNow I'm realizing there's a mismatch with how `signer_seeds` should be formatted for `invoke_signed` — it expects a slice of slices for multiple signers, but I'm only passing seeds for a single signer.\n\nLooking at the existing coinflip implementation, I can see the pattern: wrapping the single signer's seeds in an outer slice to match the expected `&[&[&[u8]]]` format. So I'll wrap `signer_seeds` when calling `invoke_signed`, and the vector allocation for building the instruction data should be fine since the Solana VM supports it.\n\nActually, I'll use a fixed-size array instead—it's cleaner to allocate 25 bytes upfront and fill in the discriminator, wager amount, won amount, and winner flag. Now I need to figure out which accounts to pass to `invoke_signed`.\n\nFor the `UpdatePlayerProfile` CPI call, I need the caller as a signer and the profile account as mutable. I should probably include the platform program too to be safe, since the runtime needs all referenced accounts. As for `total_games_delta`, the spec seems to treat it as a single increment per player, so I'll just document that this parameter is effectively ignored and move forward.\n\nWriting the implementation...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2995,"cache_read_input_tokens":53415,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2995},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c02d31dc-7289-45e7-92f4-faacb953998d","uuid":"38c58020-f66d-4ac0-ba87-cc73ffd07aa5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PuGrmGhhcnJRW6PUKzWsbk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see that `platform` depends on `rng-shared`, so adding `platform` as a dependency of `rng-shared` would create a circular dependency. I'll construct the CPI manually by building the instruction data directly, avoiding the circular dep.\n\nNow let me create the CPI module."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2995,"cache_read_input_tokens":53415,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2995},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c02d31dc-7289-45e7-92f4-faacb953998d","uuid":"8a319f9d-af57-4075-a29a-9cb38531d657"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PuGrmGhhcnJRW6PUKzWsbk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01A8htGhPGBjc7t114Q4CSk1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/cpi.rs","content":"use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse anchor_lang::solana_program::{\n    instruction::{AccountMeta, Instruction},\n    program::invoke_signed,\n};\n\n/// Calls the platform program's `update_player_profile` instruction via CPI.\n///\n/// If the profile account has no data (player hasn't created a profile), the call\n/// is silently skipped — returns `Ok(())` without emitting a CPI.\n///\n/// This helper constructs the CPI instruction manually (discriminator + borsh args)\n/// to avoid a circular dependency between `rng-shared` and `platform`.\n///\n/// # Arguments\n///\n/// * `platform_program` — The platform program account.\n/// * `profile` — The player's profile PDA (mutable). Skipped if empty.\n/// * `authority` — The game config PDA that signs the CPI.\n/// * `signer_seeds` — Seeds for PDA signing (e.g., `&[b\"coinflip_config\", &[bump]]`).\n/// * `total_games_delta` — Reserved; platform always increments by 1 per call.\n/// * `wins_delta` — If > 0, player is marked as winner.\n/// * `total_wagered_delta` — Lamports wagered in this game (maps to `wager_amount`).\n/// * `total_won_delta` — Lamports won in this game (maps to `won_amount`, 0 if lost).\n///\n/// # Example\n///\n/// ```ignore\n/// update_player_profile_cpi(\n///     &ctx.accounts.platform_program,\n///     &ctx.accounts.creator_profile,\n///     &ctx.accounts.config.to_account_info(),\n///     &[b\"coinflip_config\", &[config_bump]],\n///     1,                    // total_games_delta\n///     if is_winner { 1 } else { 0 }, // wins_delta\n///     entry_amount,         // total_wagered_delta\n///     if is_winner { payout } else { 0 }, // total_won_delta\n/// )?;\n/// ```\npub fn update_player_profile_cpi<'a>(\n    platform_program: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    profile: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    authority: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    signer_seeds: &[&[u8]],\n    _total_games_delta: u64,\n    wins_delta: u64,\n    total_wagered_delta: u64,\n    total_won_delta: u64,\n) -> Result<()> {\n    // Guard: skip if profile hasn't been created yet\n    if profile.data_is_empty() {\n        return Ok(());\n    }\n\n    // Map to platform program's actual parameters\n    let wager_amount = total_wagered_delta;\n    let won_amount = total_won_delta;\n    let is_winner = wins_delta > 0;\n\n    // Discriminator = sha256(\"global:update_player_profile\")[0..8]\n    let disc = anchor_lang::solana_program::hash::hash(b\"global:update_player_profile\");\n\n    // Instruction data: 8-byte discriminator + wager_amount(u64) + won_amount(u64) + is_winner(bool)\n    let mut data = [0u8; 25];\n    data[..8].copy_from_slice(&disc.to_bytes()[..8]);\n    data[8..16].copy_from_slice(&wager_amount.to_le_bytes());\n    data[16..24].copy_from_slice(&won_amount.to_le_bytes());\n    data[24] = u8::from(is_winner);\n\n    let accounts = vec![\n        AccountMeta::new_readonly(*authority.key, true), // caller (signer)\n        AccountMeta::new(*profile.key, false),           // profile (mutable)\n    ];\n\n    let ix = Instruction {\n        program_id: *platform_program.key,\n        accounts,\n        data: data.to_vec(),\n    };\n\n    invoke_signed(\n        &ix,\n        &[authority.clone(), profile.clone(), platform_program.clone()],\n        &[signer_seeds],\n    )?;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2995,"cache_read_input_tokens":53415,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2995},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c02d31dc-7289-45e7-92f4-faacb953998d","uuid":"cb2915a9-0c51-4757-8622-ca9a4e88351d"}
